en: Acquired by Ludwig I of Germany in 1831, as part of a large collection from the Necropolis of Vulci. In 1841 the collection was put on display in the Alte Pinakothek in Munich. After World War I, the collection was reorganized as part of the Antikensammlungen, Munich, where the Euphronios vase remains.
